communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Good morning, 

I would like to receive any and all documents (emails, presentations, internal working documents, meeting notes) related to selection of Higher Education Loan Authority of the State of Missouri otherwise known as Mohela as the 'Official servicer of federal student aid'. I would like documents that discuss the bid process for student loan companies to bid for official servicer and any documents related to Higher Education Loan Authority of the State of Missouri otherwise known as Mohela being the servicer for public service loan forgiveness. This request is related to PSLF and Federal Student Aid within US Department of Education if it helps to narrow my approach. Please reach out with any questions. 

Thanks

James C. Dziobek III

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

james dziobek

title: Arthur William "Art" Bell (Air Force Office of Special Investigations)

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any files involving, mentioning, or relating to the American broadcaster and author Arthur William "Art" Bell III (June 17, 1945 – April 13, 2018, Social Security Number 264-72-993). Bell was most notably the creator and original host of the paranormal themed radio program Coast to Coast AM.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jesse Robertson
